---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 219
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=The Art of Dying
By: Daidôji Yûsan
---
The idea most vital and essential to the samurai is that of death,
which he ought to have before his mind day and night, night and day,
from the dawn of the first day of the year till the last minute of the
last day of it.
